React -  Javascript library

Library:
   Libraries provide developers with predefined functions and classes to make their work easier and boost the development process. 
Framework:
   Framework, on the other hand, is like the foundation upon which developers build applications for specific platforms.
 
  For Checking whether nodejs is installed or not : node -v or node --version

Commands for vscode terminal:
   npx create-react-app filename  (it will throw a warning if you are not running the latest version. follow the instructions and uninstall ,next again run the command ).


Components :  all he parts which want to reuse 
Paths      :  all the different paths

Router is a package -> which routes the url 

